Package supermarket.domain.supermarket

Class Store

java.lang.Object
supermarket.domain.supermarket.Store
public class Store extends Object
Represents a store in the supermarket domain. The Store class allows management of shelves and products within the store.

      public void discardOfferedProduct(int productBarcode)

      Parameters:
      productBarcode - The barcode of the product to discard.

    • swapPositions

      public void swapPositions(int shelfId, int position1, int position2)
      Swaps the products at two specified positions on a shelf.

      position1 - The position of the first product.
      position2 - The position of the second product.

    • placeProducts

      public void placeProducts(Integer shelfId, ProductInfo[] productInfos)
      Places a list of products on a specified shelf (from position 0 to the size of productsOfShelf). This will override all shelf products at the placed positions. If the array size is larger than the shelf size, it will ignore the ones in the end, and show a warning.
      Parameters:
      shelfId - The ID of the shelf where the product will be placed.
      productInfos - The info of the products to place.

    • modifyShelfSize

      public void modifyShelfSize(int shelfId, int shelfSize)
      Modifies the size of a shelf. If the new size is smaller than the current size, the products that are removed will be added to the set of placeable products.
      Parameters:
      shelfId - The ID of the shelf to modify.
      shelfSize - The new size of the shelf.

    • containsProducts

      public boolean containsProducts(int shelfId)
      Returns a boolean indicating if the shelf contains any products.
      Parameters:
      shelfId - ID of the shelf that will get the products stored in
      Returns:
      True if the shelf contains any products, false otherwise.
